<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-2948] classloading weird issue</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2948</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have such thing working in our CI environment but couldn&apos;t figure out why is it not working when done from command line.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;download &lt;a href=&quot;http://anonsvn.jboss.org/repos/repository.jboss.org/maven2/jboss/jbossall-client/4.2.2.GA/jbossall-client-4.2.2.GA.jar&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://anonsvn.jboss.org/repos/repository.jboss.org/maven2/jboss/jbossall-client/4.2.2.GA/jbossall-client-4.2.2.GA.jar&lt;/a&gt; to jbossall-client.jar&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;groovy -cp jbossall-client.jar groovy_bug.groovy&quot; works fine&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;ant -f groovy_bug.xml&quot; throws an exception although task&apos;s classpath is set and otherwise classes from jbossall-client.jar are resolved:&lt;br/&gt;
javax.naming.NoInitialContextException: Cannot instantiate class: org.jnp.interfaces.NamingContextFactory &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Root exception is java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: org.jnp.interfaces.NamingContextFactory&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;ant -lib . -f groovy_bug.xml&quot; works fine.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
